parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and other components, and potentially causing a loss of vehicle control or an accident.
symptoms: Antifreeze odor coming from the vents
film build-up of antifreeze on the front glass

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame can cause the seat to tilt or move unexpectedly, which can lead to driver distraction, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver and/or passenger seat tilts or moves unexpectedly
the seat feels unstable or loose
the seat does not stay in its adjusted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail light assembly can reduce the vehicle's visibility to other drivers, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The tail lights do not function
the tail lights are dim or flickering
the tail lights are completely dark
the turn signals do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Solder Point Failure in Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the solder points in the tail light assembly can cause the tail lights to malfunction, reducing the vehicle's visibility to other drivers and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The tail lights do not function
the tail lights are dim or flickering
the tail lights are completely dark
the turn signals do not function.
